# Trivy ignore file for MSF4J
# Only CVE IDs are recognized; file paths must go in trivy.yaml

# --- BouncyCastle (Java 8 constraint, cannot use jdk18on) ---
# bcpkix-jdk15on: fixed only in 1.79 which requires jdk18on/Java 11+
CVE-2025-8916
# bcprov-jdk15on: no fix available in any version (status: affected)
CVE-2023-33201

# --- Spring Framework 5.3.39 (EOL; all fixes require Spring 6 / Java 17) ---
# spring-web HttpInvokerServiceExporter deserialization — MSF4J does NOT use this class
CVE-2016-1000027
# spring-core Annotation Detection — fixed only in 6.2.11
CVE-2025-41249
# spring-context/web DataBinder pattern bypass — fixed only in 6.1.14
CVE-2024-38820
# spring-context locale bypass — fixed only in 6.1.20
CVE-2025-22233

# --- Apache Thrift (transitive from Carbon analytics, not directly upgradable) ---
CVE-2018-1320
CVE-2019-0205
CVE-2018-11798

# --- Hystrix/Archaius transitives (EOL libraries, no fix available) ---
# commons-configuration 1.x — no fix; only 2.x (different artifact) has fix
CVE-2025-46392
# commons-lang 2.x — no fix for 2.x; production code uses commons-lang3 3.18.0
CVE-2025-48924
